cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MED, cs.IR 

This paper involves the use of computer vision and deep learning techniques for medical imaging analysis, which suggests that it could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories. 

cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category, as the paper focuses on the development of a computer-aided framework for differential diagnosis of pancreatic cysts using convolutional neural networks. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely, as the paper involves the use of deep learning techniques to learn high-level features from medical images. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category, as the paper involves the use of AI methods for medical imaging analysis. 

cs.MED (Medical Imaging) is a relevant category, as the paper involves the analysis of medical images for the purpose of differential diagnosis of pancreatic cysts. 

cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also a possible category, as the paper involves the use of saliency maps to assist physicians in understanding the decision of the deep learning method.
